4 HR____ HONORING THE DISTINGUISHED CAREER OF SUSIE HEIRD.
5
6 WHEREAS, Susie Heird has rendered exemplary service
7 to the Shoals region and the State of Alabama through her
8 long-standing commitment to economic development; and
9 WHEREAS, Susie Heird was among the original employees
10 of the Shoals Economic Development Authority (SEDA) at its
11 founding in 1986, demonstrating vision, courage, and
12 dedication at a pivotal moment in the organization's
13 history; and
14 WHEREAS, over the course of more than four decades,
15 she has played an integral role in guiding SEDA through
16 significant growth, transformation, and success, helping to
17 shape the organization into the impactful and respected
18 institution it is today; and
19 WHEREAS, her career has been defined by unwavering
20 dedication, exceptional professionalism, and the highest
21 standards of integrity, earning the respect and admiration
22 of colleagues, community leaders, and partners throughout
23 the region; and
24 WHEREAS, Susie Heird has been a cornerstone of
25 economic development efforts in the Shoals from the very
26 beginning, contributing not only her expertise but also her
27 steadfast commitment to the prosperity and advancement of
28 the community; and
Page 1

the community; and
HR350 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, even after transitioning into a part-time
30 and advisory role following 30 years of distinguished
31 full-time service, she continues to make invaluable daily
32 contributions to the organization's ongoing success,
33 offering wisdom, guidance, and leadership that remain
34 essential to its mission; and
35 WHEREAS, her legacy endures through the lasting
36 impact of her work, as her leadership and influence continue
37 to be reflected in the progress and achievements of the
38 Shoals Economic Development Authority today; now therefore,
39 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE
40 LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, That we do hereby recognize and
41 honor Susie Heird for her outstanding career, her enduring
42 contributions to economic development, and her steadfast
43 service to the Shoals region and the State of Alabama.
44 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That we extend our deepest
45 appreciation and best wishes for her continued success and
46 fulfillment in all her future endeavors.
